Pour the @water{300%ml}(for the rice) into a #medium saucepan{} with a tight-fitting
#lid{}. Stir in the @Jasmine rice{150%g} and @salt{1/4%tsp} and bring to the boil.
Once boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered)
and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice
will continue to cook in its own steam).

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in another #large saucepan{} on medium-high
heat.

Once hot, add the @sliced mushrooms{80%g} to the pan and season with @salt{}
and @pepper{}. Cook until slightly browned, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Meanwhile, cut the @lime{1} into wedges. Drain the @king prawns{150%g}.

Once the mushrooms have browned, stir in the @diced British chicken breast{240%g},
@coconut milk{200%ml}, @Thai style spice mix{1%sachet} (add less if you'd prefer
things milder), @Thai green style paste{45%g}, @chicken stock paste{10%g} and
@sugar{1/2%tsp}.

Bring to a boil, then lower the heat and simmer until the chicken is cooked
through, ~{10-12%minutes}. Halfway through cooking, stir in the prawns, then
cook for another ~{5-6%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat and fish and
> their packaging. The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.
> The prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.

When the curry's ready, squeeze in half the lime juice from the lime wedges.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed. Add a splash of water if
you feel it needs it.

Fluff up your rice with a #fork{} and share between your #serving bowls{}.
Spoon over your Thai green style chicken and prawn curry.

Serve any remaining lime wedges alongside for squeezing over. Enjoy!